.TH JTUTIL-SPLIT16 "1" "April 2026" "jtutil-split16 manual" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
jtutil-split16 \- Split 16-bit ROM images into 8-bit halves
.SH DESCRIPTION
16\-bit memories are normally implemented as two 8\-bit memories.
In order to load a default value from a file, you need to split the file in
two halves. The new files add _lo and _hi to the name.
The files are created in the current folder, but can be read from any path.
.SS "Usage:"
.IP
jtutil split16 <files> [flags]
.SS "Flags:"
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
help for split16
.TP
\fB\-s\fR, \fB\-\-swap\fR
swaps lo and hi files
.SS "Global Flags:"
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Verbose
